description.p: A small (film canister sized, approx.) cache at a lakeside.
Stealth is required to avoid detection from muggles

long-description.p: Bring your own writing tool to sign the log. (On the day this cache was placed, we did our own "CITO" around the area, only to notice our good work being undone by a crow! He was picking the rubbish back out of the bins, & we had been blaming the humans :) )

ul.li:
2010-06-13T19:00:00Z : Found it by RosMcC
Searched for five minutes with no luck, then himself got out of the car and found it in seconds. Makes you mad, doesn't it? SL, then fed the birds. Thanks. Took Tweety coin.

2010-06-10T19:00:00Z : Write note by thomasvm
Dropped tweety coin in.

2010-06-09T19:00:00Z : Found it by thomasvm
Found it on second visit - thanks Abbey. Was probably touching it on my first visit. Dropped a coin in. TFTC.
This entry was edited by thomasvm on Thursday, 10 June 2010 at 06:43:25.

2010-05-29T19:00:00Z : Found it by BlueFoxPL
Another great day for caching... found with some friends. TFTC.

2010-05-29T19:00:00Z : Found it by Wicca Cailín
Lovely spot but lots of people about. After a little waiting the coast was clear. The swans were very curious as to what we were up to though [:D] Third find of ten this evening with Adam. Great fun. TFTC
In: Mountain Goat Toy Out: Geocoin
